content: {'id': '2426d52b-1955-335b-8665-aa81bf9ec5fd', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': 'India’s NTPC flags risks to coal plant lifespan from reduced load', 'description': '', 'summary': "NEW DELHI (Reuters) -NTPC Ltd, India's largest coal power generator, has raised concerns that operating coal-fired power plants at a reduced load could significantly shorten the lifespan of its units.  The Central Electricity Authority (CEA), the country's de facto advisor for the power ministry, has recommended lowering the technical minimum — the lowest level at which a thermal plant can run reliably — to 40% of its installed capacity to help accommodate rising renewable energy generation.  This shift is part of India's broader strategy to integrate more solar and wind power into the grid while maintaining round-the-clock supply.", 'pubDate': '2025-09-02T12:03:32Z', 'displayTime': '2025-09-02T12:03:32Z', 'isHosted': True, 'bypassModal': False, 'previewUrl': None, 'thumbnail': {'originalUrl': 'https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/fb5a4d3ced25d96a04bc47b96f1fbefd', 'originalWidth': 800, 'originalHeight': 523, 'caption': 'A signboard of NTPC (National Thermal Power Corporation Limited) is seen outside its office in Mumbai', 'resolutions': [{'url': 'https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/iWYdGSIEylZXlS4oBdtTlg--~B/aD01MjM7dz04MDA7YXBwaWQ9eXRhY2h5b24-/https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/fb5a4d3ced25d96a04bc47b96f1fbefd', 'width': 800, 'height': 523, 'tag': 'original'}, {'url': 'https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/pC7z3sasL_D73rLqW2e.dA--~B/Zmk9c3RyaW07aD0xMjg7dz0xNzA7YXBwaWQ9eXRhY2h5b24-/https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/fb5a4d3ced25d96a04bc47b96f1fbefd', 'width': 170, 'height': 128, 'tag': '170x128'}]}, 'provider': {'displayName': 'Reuters', 'url': 'https://www.reuters.com/'}, 'canonicalUrl': {'url': 'https://sg.finance.yahoo.com/news/india-ntpc-flags-risks-coal-120332205.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'SG', 'lang': 'en-SG'}, 'clickThroughUrl': {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/india-ntpc-flags-risks-coal-120332205.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'US', 'lang': 'en-US'}, 'metadata': {'editorsPick': False}, 'finance': {'premiumFinance': {'isPremiumNews': False, 'isPremiumFreeNews': False}}, 'storyline': None}

content: {'id': 'c6a105d0-c727-3a74-b253-8dda32941b74', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India's NALCO to invest $3.43 billion to build smelter, coal power plant", 'description': '', 'summary': "NEW DELHI (Reuters) -India's National Aluminium Company (NALCO) will invest a total of 300 billion rupees ($3.43 billion) in a new smelter and a coal power plant over the next five years, Chairman and Managing Director Brijendra Pratap Singh said on Thursday.  The state-run aluminium producer will budget roughly 180 billion rupees to set up the proposed smelter in the eastern Indian state of Odisha, Singh told reporters in New Delhi.  The remaining 120 billion rupees will be used to set up a coal power plant, for which it is in talks with Coal India and NTPC, Singh said.", 'pubDate': '2025-08-28T13:22:46Z', 'displayTime': '2025-08-28T13:22:46Z', 'isHosted': True, 'bypassModal': False, 'previewUrl': None, 'thumbnail': None, 'provider': {'displayName': 'Reuters', 'url': 'https://www.reuters.com/'}, 'canonicalUrl': {'url': 'https://sg.finance.yahoo.com/news/indias-nalco-invest-3-43-132246174.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'SG', 'lang': 'en-SG'}, 'clickThroughUrl': {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/indias-nalco-invest-3-43-132246174.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'US', 'lang': 'en-US'}, 'metadata': {'editorsPick': False}, 'finance': {'premiumFinance': {'isPremiumNews': False, 'isPremiumFreeNews': False}}, 'storyline': None}

content: {'id': '42fda329-2129-376b-ba6c-e60f83ee5cf3', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India's two state-run firms to issue over $500 million of debt in August, sources say", 'description': '', 'summary': 'MUMBAI (Reuters) -Indian state-run companies NHPC and NTPC Green Energy will raise around 45 billion rupees (about $512.6 million) through the sale of short-term bonds this month, three sources aware of the matter said on Tuesday.
